# DA-7: Architectural Consistency
VERSION: 1.2.0
PRIORITY: SYSTEM
SCOPE: Any new pattern, abstraction, or structural approach — whether differing from an established convention or introduced where no convention yet exists.

## CATEGORY CONTEXT
- Established Convention: A pattern, abstraction, or structural approach already used across the codebase and documented or recognised as the standard approach.
- Justified Deviation: A deliberate departure from an established convention that is documented, approved, and either extends or replaces the convention intentionally.
- Architectural Drift: Gradual, unintentional divergence from established conventions due to undocumented deviations.
- No Established Convention: A pattern area where no prior usage, ADR, or documented standard exists in the codebase.

ENFORCE: If established convention exists: new patterns must match it or carry documented, approved justification. If no convention exists: ask the user for their preferred approach before implementing — do not assume or default silently. This check applies at every decision point during execution, not only at pre-execution.
ALLOW: Justified deviations when the existing pattern is identified technical debt targeted for replacement.
PROHIBIT: Silent divergence from conventions; parallel implementations of the same concept in different patterns; silently assuming an implementation approach when no convention exists.
ON VIOLATION: convention_mismatch → escalate to Design Review Skill → require remediation before merge. convention_replacement → halt until migration plan documented. no_convention → ask_user_preference → block until confirmed.
